headline.main: Erich Maria Remarque Is Dead; Novels Recorded Agony of War; Erich Maria Remarque, Novelist, Dies

snippet: GENEVA, Sept. 25--Erich Maria Remarque, the Germanborn author who attained world fame with his World War I novel "All Quiet on the Western Front," died at noon today of a heart collapse at the Sant Agnese clinic at Locarno, Switzerland. He was 72 ...
